      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/126/5548",
      "text": [
        " : \"أَعْتَقَ أَبُو جَعْفَرٍ عَلَيْهِ اَلسَّلاَمُ مِنْ غِلْمَانِهِ عِنْدَ مَوْتِهِ شِرَارَهُمْ وَ أَمْسَكَ خِيَارَهُمْ فَقُلْتُ لَهُ يَا أَبَتِ تُعْتِقُ هَؤُلاَءِ وَ تُمْسِكُ هَؤُلاَءِ فَقَالَ \"إِنَّهُمْ قَدْ أَصَابُوا مِنِّي ضَرْباً فَيَكُونُ هَذَا بِهَذَا\" \"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.5548 - Muhammad ibn Ya'qub Al-Kulayni, may Allah (swt) be pleased with him, narrated from Humayd ibn Ziyad from Al-Hasan ibn Muhammad ibn Sama'ah from Abdullah ibn Jabalah and others from Ishaq ibn Ammar from Abu Basir from Abu Abdullah (as), who said:\n\"Abu Jafar Imam Muhammad ibn Ali Al-Baqir (as), freed the worst of his servants at the time of his death and kept the best of them.\nI (Al-Sadiq (as)) said to him (Al-Baqir (as)): 'O' my father, you are freeing these and keeping those?'\nHe (Al Baqir (as)) replied: ''They have suffered beatings from me, so this is to balance that (their wrongdoings).'\""
        ]
      }
    },
